They filled their waters and had water while we still had no water as well. We even had some guy from the store next door come up and yell at my friend that they didn't have something she wanted to order-turns out he doesn't work there but he acted like it and made her feel very uncomfortable. We decided to sit at the window with our luggage under us. We put in our orders and waited as a couple of groups also came in. When we arrived everyone there had been served so there shouldn’t have been much ahead of our order. After waiting 30 minutes for eggs and bacon to cook I noticed our food was sitting on their counter awaiting our server. I walked over and asked if I could help and take our meals so we could finally eat. The server seemed flustered and curtly let me know they would bring it over when they were done. Having already waited for a significant amount of time, I decided I no longer wished to wait around and eat breakfast (I could get anywhere) served late and rudely. The rest of my party did stay and informed me it was an average breakfast.

Overall: An almost-upscale diner option that is unique to the area.  The good: The dishes are large and delicious; the country-fried pork and "tamales" were both filling and flavorful. We had a few leftovers as a result, and they were still great a second time. The pork was tender on the inside but crunchy on the outside, and it was covered in delicious gravy but not swimming in it. The peas were a nice addition.  The not-so-good: After we ordered, the food took quite a while to come out. And unfortunately the service started off ok, but it faded rather quickly and we had to wait awhile for the check. And, the prices aren't too "diner-y", and are more on the expensive side.  Food/drink: 8/10 Atmosphere: 8/10 Service: 7/10

Overall the meal was great but I will say the $10 bloody mary was expensive for the quality. Good service, Katie gave me the morning pep I needed. Check it out.
Delicious food and creative menu. Seating is casual with long tables and bar stools.

I wish I had 4 thumbs so I could give 🕊s four 👍🏿 !!! Food is outstanding! Anytime we come menu items may change and present a flavor rotation which is exciting and intriguing to experience.ESP w the seasons of chi... all accompanying condiments are outstanding and home made including their special paste (don’t know what it’s called but it’s made of 🌶 and garlic and sure is 😋!) I put all 3 ( the clear , the red and the paste) on any item and it brings out the flavors. ❤️
Really interesting food combos, tastes and flavors. Not many tables so groups can be problematic. Very popular and question the noisy when busy. Full, well-stocked bar.
Super food & fun wait staff!
Country Ham Tamal. The name doesn't do it justice. Awesome balance of textures and flavors and perfectly portioned. Would love to go back and try something else!

Mr. Kahan and his amazing team never cease to impress. Incredible food; thoughtfully, creatively and passionately prepared. Welcoming service by casual and knowledge staff. The chicken fried chicken is easily the top 2 or 3 chicken dishes I've ever had in my life!

Homey, delicious, lively and really good service. It’s a great place in a great neighborhood. Only a few minutes from the 606 walkway. We had the Burnt End Hash and avocado salad. Delicious. Also nice homemade jam and a wonderful, smokey salsa condiment. Put it on everything!
Tremendous esoteric mezcal selection, great Tex-Mex, lovely staff. One of my favorites.

Always have a good time here. Music is always good and the staff are really friendly and attentive.  I usually get the chicken but decided to try the burnt ends hash today. Was really good. Didn't have to wait today as we got there a little before noon.

Right off the Blue in Wicker Park, this place is amazing! Come before 1030 and there’s no wait. We had bloody Maria’s (spicy and awesome with a beer back), the Tamal, and the Coppa de Puerco and everything was amazing. Great service, solid people watching, out of the park food. Use the nutty chili sauce (paste?) on the table - is unique and fun.
Amazing food and great tasting menu. It's a great way to get an overall idea of the menu for when you come back next!
Great setting, nice food
Do yourself a favor and get the Chicken Fried Chicken. The portion is enough for two. And the wild card ingredient in the dish—peas! So good.
Delicious peach pancake, great service, good atmosphere on a Monday morning!
Eggplant & peaches lunch must have been designed by a very creative chef. Hostess and bartender were helpful and very charming. Definately will recommend to friends & family.
Had really good brunch, and unlimited coffee. Nice place.
Very slow service, but good food. Avoid the ceviche, though.

Really cute space, steps away from the Damen blue line station. The wait for two at ten am on a Saturday was only ten minutes. Given the space larger groups may be hard to accommodate. The noise level was fairly moderate even when packed, I could easily hold a conversation with the friend I was with. Ordered coffee and the buttermilk pancake stuffed with blood oranges, which was killer. They also have good gluten free and meat free options and ask about allergies.  Update, went back for early dinner. Was a bit disappointed in the pickle plate but the pepper hash was pretty great. Not to mention wonderful happy hour drink options.

What can I say, other than AMAZING. The food is really good. If you need recommendations, ask them.

The place is great, the food not so much. Texas-bbq style meats are not that great, the Mac & Cheese I had was basically just overcooked pasta. I hear that the breakfast is excellent, but still have to try it.
Great food / great drink and awesome staff
Great place, awesome breakfast Totally recommended.
Got to love a good diner
Had a wonderful time at Dove's. Food was outstanding and the service was good. Loooooved the chicken fried chicken, makes me want to eat peas a bit more frequently.

I was doubtful when I looked at the menu, I was worried I was going to get an expensive small plate for breakfast and I was hungry. I was pleasantly surprised by the quality and quantity of the breakfast! I got the burnt tips hash, and my girlfriend got the tofu toast. Everything was really good, priced reasonably, fast service. Would definitely go back.
Good food, service is decent. Not so spectacular that I'd go out of my way for it, but a solid, consistent choice.
Hip, fun spot. Will bring friends for brunch.
My favorite brunch spot in the city.
The Coppa de puerco is seriously amazing... and they serve dark matter coffee so what else could you ask for. Delicious!
Great food and atmosphere
Favorite brunch space. Fried chicken with peas and gravy and a side of potatoes
Very cute restaurant! Food was delicious and not over priced, with good portions. Staff was very attentive and friendly!

Great food ans service
The food was good, but not good enough to justify the wait and the cost

Hear Ye, Hear Ye- Just so happened to want a small bite before an appointment on a Saturday morning when I stopped in to Dove’s Luncheonette. The hostess Megan welcomed me with a big, bright smile and I was hooked already. I asked to see a menu and scoured it for my must have favorite food anytime of day.....A Biscuit. After being told by both Megan and an also very welcoming waitress Sarah that couldn’t order to go at the hostess desk, I was directed to the bar. I immediately made eye contact with the instantly asinine (I’ll get to the reason for calling him that in a sec.) waiter Sam who totally ignored me for several minutes and went on to help two customers who were seated. Sometimes you just know it’s about to get interesting, right? I get first come, first serve but being a former bartender and waitress, at least acknowledge the costumer! He took their order in an oh so pleasant tone, place it into the system and walked oh so slowly away and then back to me and exhaled as if bothered and asked what I needed. Despite his negative ora, I said hello and asked for two biscuits without gravy. Not sure why but he seemed taken aback by my order, rolled his eyes then proceeded to ring me up. When he returned with my receipt, it wasn’t surprising to read Two Biscuits W/Gravy. I simply reiterated that did NOT want gravy when Mr. Not So Happy Saturday blew up. The waitress Sarah noticed his terrible demeanor and immediately stepped in to assist. He hissed something to the effect of “...you can take care of that..” and she obliged, apologized on behalf of him and the establishment and rang me up. First of all, thank you Megan and Sarah for being so warm and inviting. Because of you, I was able to contain my Gangsta Girl physical and mental state. To anyone who is familiar with this establishment, please pass on both the positive and negative experience I have shared. As a person who resides in the neighborhood, doesn’t really cook, loves a recommendation and appreciates great food and service, it’s the little things that mean so much. Remember that.... -Tosh
Good place to hang out

What a great place for brunch/lunch.  I had the oatmeal.  It came with blueberries and gooseberries and lots of nuts.  I also had and a yogurt parfait with fruit and granola.  It was seasoned with Santa Fe pepper flakes.  It was amazing, but perhaps a little too spicy.  The portions are generous. My wife had a small plate of vegetarian hash.  She added avocado to it.  She was only able to eat half of it.  We took the rest home.  My daughter had the enchiladas.  They were covered with delicious mole sauce.  They looked and tasted fantastic.  Again she was able to save some for later.  One negative, if you can call it that.  Both the menu on Google and on the website are out of dates. The website is closer. What this means is they are changing up the menu you to provide you a fresh new experience.  I plan on going back to see what's new vet soon. Yummy!
Great vibes and great brunch at this place! I visited it only once but I'd definitely go back!
There is always a pleasure to come to this place
Great for brunch. Beeen there a number of times and and never been disappointed.
Wow!
Excellent Mexican fusion diner. Do a mezcal flight!

Fantastic Mexican themed breakfast/brunch place from the same folks that run Big Star next door. The interior vibe says diner, but the food is inventive and delicious. Don’t miss the blood sausage with crispy chicken skin, $10 fried chicken and beer specials, or the hot sauce (you can take some home for $8).
So much fun you must go

Delicious. I had the country fried chicken. Make sure to give yourself enough time because the diner sized place fills up quickly. Well worth the wait. They also play random records all day so waiting isn't too bad
Amazing food! Everything my hubby and I have tried on the brunch menu has been so flavorful and scrumptious.
Chicken friend chicken is INCREDIBLE!!!

Finally made it in here after walking by for nearly two years. Went around 9am on a Saturday, so we were immediately seated. Coffee was hot and good. All of the food we had was delicious. The Breakfast Cemita puts every other breakfast sandwich to shame. It was perfect. We also got the Buttermilk Pancake which was more than worth the extra 15 minutes they request to prepare it (though I don't even think it took that long). Good music and good coffee too, can't wait to come back.
The chicken fried chicken, with chorizo green chili country gravy was the absolute best. Had a spicy cocktail to round out the meal. Oh my gosh so good.
Great menu terrific food if a little busy
The best place ever. Have the Unión Mezcal.
Food was only ok and service was slow. Cool atmosphere and good specials on tequila!

Consistently excellent, inventive food in a cool atmosphere. Weekday breakfast is quiet and peaceful. I’d say the only downside is that they don’t do espresso-based drinks. But that’s easily rectified with a visit to La Colombe across the street.

Food was ok, I liked the service and the potato pepper hash. The chicken fried chicken and the brisket taco weren't amazing.

I also tried the fried chicken that my friend ordered and that was very tasty, so if I go back I’ll definitely be ordering that instead. It’s a cute spot and perhaps I just ordered the wrong item for my tastes.
Great breakfast. Great music.
Loved the music and the ambience. The bartender is awesome. Food was ok  - I had the fried chicken. I would definitely come back
I love all the food here and the atmosphere is great!

Amazing flavors in everything here. Anything I have ever had from here has exceeded expectations.  Super casual but very trendy. Not cheap compared to other "diner" style places but very well worth the money.
Cozy atmosphere Fun to sit at the counter while listening to vinyl records. They have an amazing selection of tequila so the first drinks they make are fantastic

Great food. They had a really good chicken and beer deal. Very tasty. Also,they are conveniently located right next to a subway station
This place is very unique,  the flavors , the service,  the music,  the everything is just so good ,

The pickle platter is odd but if you’re a fan of pickled anything, this really hits it out of the park. The drinks had good ingredients and were made to our specifications. I recommend the michelada.

First rate retro/remodeled diner. This place reminds me of a home I wish I had. It’s charming hopeful interior sparks a welcome passion for nostalgia. Excellent happy hour with truly engaged severs. Can’t go wrong.
Fantastic menu. Food is superb. Very chill ambience.
Low key one of the best restaurants in the city.
This place was outstanding. I need to come back. Great service. Unique food.
Best fried chicken breakfast. I wish I hadn't found out about this.

Ordered the arugula salad with an egg on top and the breakfast cemita. Both were fantastic! Best salad I’ve had in a long time- so much flavour!! 3$ bottomless drip coffee and great service. Bill was 28$ total for 2 people—reasonably priced given the quality of the food. Would go again and recommend to a friend!
Loves Doves!
Love going for brunch here. Such great flavours and exciting dishes. Great atmosphere and decor too.

Always consistently great. They have a great menu and they're open early for breakfast, unlike a lot of the local brunch spots that don't open until 10. Their location is super convenient (across from the Damen Blue Line). Their specials are really good, but so is their Burnt Ends Hash, one of my personal favorites! If you're an early riser, Dove's doesn't get packed until later in the morning, so it's usually no wait from 8:30-9:45am

Small Tex-Mex spot that packs quickly. I met a friend here for lunch this past weekend, and we both really enjoyed it. We were told it'd be about a half-hour wait, but less than 10 minutes later we were seated. I decided on this spot because I heard good things about the Bloody Mary's, which were pretty damn tasty. We both got the tequila Bloody Mary, and it came with a beer chaser. I had the pozole, and I enjoyed it. I could've used a bit more, especially since the bowl is so humongous, but I was satisfied nonetheless. My buddy got the cemita and he seemed to have enjoyed it.  I'd definitely stop in again in the future. The menu looks great and I'd like to try some other items.

Half hipster nouveau dinner, half throwback luncheonette counter, and it's works perfectly. Friendly service, superlative coffee, excellent dishes, priced less than you'd expect. And really tasteful interesting music soundtrack from a vinyl turntable. Get here and eat.

A rotating staple as one of our go-to spots. The BF loves the burger that is not featured in the regular menu but a menu board item. The spicy sesame salsa is addictive and tastes good on just about everything. I love the seafood selections and ceviche. Pozole is OK.

Loved this place! Every seat in the house is like sitting at a bar. They always have a good record (yes it really is a record) playing. The chicken fried chicken is out of this world!

Went for brunch. Small place with good music, mezcal and craft beer, and a cool menu that combines elements of Mexican and Southern cuisines. It was hard to decide what to order because so many items looked good. The food was awesome and …

My fiancé and I went to Dove’s for dinner on 1/21 and it was a disappointment. I ordered a Bloody Mary and I have to say it was one of the worst I have ever had. I do not know what the base mixture was but it was awful. My fiancé ordered the brisket entree and it was a flop as well. One piece of the brisket was all fat and no beef. When there was actually beef it was flavorless. I ordered the Pozole and it was not what I expected. There was literally 5 chunks of pork with 3 of the 5 pieces being half fat. I had to fish for the hominy in the dish. When I think of and have had pozole in the past it is/was a hearty dish. This was not. The only saving grace of the dinner were the grits. We actually paid and went to the Big Star street window service next door because we were still hungry and got a good meal. My biggest complaint other than food quality would be your treatment of cilantro in the dishes. You are supposed to pluck the cilantro leaves from the stems. At Dove’s they leave the stems on which is unsavory. Save your money and go somewhere else.
I was hoping the food was going to be as good as big star but it honestly wasn't anything special.

We stumbled upon this place on a weekend visit to Chicago, looking for a hangover breakfast cure, and it DELIVERED. Our server was so friendly and helpful, guiding us to the best drink option (A+ slap you back to reality Bloody Marias), and the food was plentiful and delicious. Would definitely recommend, post a night of over indulging or not.

As we arrived the place was full but they took our phone number and as soon as a table was available they texted us.  The service was good as well as the food,  wish there were more vegetarian options.  Place is small so be ready to share the space.
Nice place

Service was great, food was delicious, and the diner vibe didn't come across as tacky despite the fact that it's filled with a Sunday brunch crowd. We had the chicken fried chicken and pozole rojo and enjoyed both, but everything on the menu looks good.

Great little spot with delicious food :) the ambiance is great and the vibe is hip and trendy. Dove’s breakfast was amazing and quite delicious. The food was hot, fresh and very tasty!  I loved the Burnt Ends Hash with the eggs over medium.  So good! The pancake was crazy good, and so big we couldn’t finish it. The small old school diner vibe is very cool. Also, they have a large variety of drinks to choose from :) we are definitely going back and strongly recommend it.

Food was just ok. Dove plate and salmon toast. The toast had way too many flavors going on to get any distinct taste. Weird combination. The eggs were nothing special. Kinda plain. Staff was friendly and atmosphere was cool.

Im not very interested in their mexican style menu... Tortas and brisket yadda yadda But The Chicken Fried Chicken is Amazing! Uggg I love it. Its the only thing ill order when im there with a side of hash of course. So good.NOTHING

One of my favorite restaurants in Chicago. I go almost every Wednesday!
Great food. Always has great daily specials.
A neighborhood gem. Awesome spot for people watching and a unique twist on comfort food.

Amazing food and staff! The chicken fried chicken is to die for!
Favorite brunch place, chicken fried chicken and burnt ends and the pancake are my favorites
Everything here is delicious!

Mezcal Maria was bloody excellent. Nice smoky flavor. The bloody comes with a little beer on the side. I added a fried egg to the pepper and potatoes with scallions, and they were delicious and filling. Potatoes crisp on the outside and soft on the inside.
Sooo good.

Creative place and an energetic vibe. Great service and wonderful flavors during a busy Saturday lunch. Check out their weekend specials. Every 1st sunday of the month they host a special dinner menu featuring Cuban favorites.
Love. Lillian is the coolest server/person ever.

Food was good but definitely crowded and cramped seating. Nice atmosphere though.
Delicious food, down to earth service and a fantastic Mezcal selection.
Not your usual Mexican. Friendly service. Order the shrimp and chorizo.
Fabulous!  Order everything on the menu!
